Indonesia Stock Movers: Citra Marga, Gas Negara, Medco Energi

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-09-06T09:40:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/indonesia-stock-movers-citra-marga-gas-negara-medco-energi.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 23.80 points, or 0.6
percent, to 3,889.97, advancing for a second day.  PT Citra Marga Nusaphala Persada (CMNP IJ), a toll-road
operator, gained 5.6 percent to 1,700 rupiah, the highest close
since Feb. 26, 2008. The government plans to raise the tariff
rates on 13 toll roads in September, Ahmad Gani Gazali, head of
the nation’s toll-road regulator at the Ministry of Public
Works, said in a statement on the ministry’s website.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ),  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed oil company, rose 3.2 percent to 2,400 rupiah,
the sharpest gain since Aug. 11. Medco is preparing to resume
operations at its Area 47 oil block in  Libya  as it plans to
reopen its office in the North African country as soon as this
week, President Director Lukman Mahfoedz said in an e-mailed
statement late yesterday.  PT Perusahaan Gas Negara (PGAS IJ), Indonesia’s biggest
distributor of the fuel, slid 0.9 percent to 2,750 rupiah, the
lowest close since May 26, 2009. BPMigas, the nation’s oil and
gas regulator, has asked Gas Negara to buy the fuel from
domestic producers at a higher price of more than $3 per million
British thermal units, R. Priyono, BPMigas chairman, said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
